from pathlib import Path
import base64, json, hashlib, gzip

target_path = Path('/mnt/data').joinpath('src/outputs/eval_loop.py')
assert target_path.is_file(), 'Expected src/outputs/eval_loop.py to exist before export'
data = target_path.read_bytes()
payload = {
   'path': 'src/outputs/eval_loop.py',
   'size': len(data),
   'encoding': 'base64',
   'sha256': hashlib.sha256(data).hexdigest(),
   'content': None
}
if len(data) > 20000:
    compressed = gzip.compress(data)
    payload['encoding'] = 'gzip+base64'
    payload['content'] = base64.b64encode(compressed).decode('ascii')
else:
    payload['content'] = base64.b64encode(data).decode('ascii')

file_export_line = 'FILE_EXPORT:' + json.dumps(payload, separators=(',', ':'))
dir_state_line = 'DIR_STATE:' + json.dumps(sorted(str(p.relative_to(Path("/mnt/data"))) for p in target_path.parent.glob('*') if p.is_file()))
file_export_line[:100], dir_state_line
